<figureCitation box="[278,303,1981,2007]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1721]" captionTargetId="figure-167@33.[151,1436,489,1725]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 11. Encrinurella insangensis (Reed) from the Li-Lu and Kunlein Formations (Katian), northern Shan State, Myanmar. 1a, b. Cranidium (original of Reed 1915, pl. 8, fig. 16), GSI 11562, Hweyawt, original and retrodeforamtion. 2. Cranidium (original of Reed 1915, pl. 8, fig. 15), GSI 11561, Mân-ngai. 3. Cranidium (original of Reed 1915, pl. 8, fig. 18), GSI 11564, Makmongshai. 4. Cranidium (original of Reed 1906, pl. 5, fig. 24), GSI 8338, Kun-lein. 5. Pygidium (original of Reed 1915, pl. 8, fig. 19), GSI 11565, Mân-ngai. 6. Pygidium (original of Reed 1915, pl. 8, fig. 20), GSI 11566, Mân-ngai. 7. Pygidium (original of Reed 1906, pl. 5, fig. 20), GSI 8336, Insang. 8. Thorax (original of Reed 1906, pl. 5, fig. 25), GSI 8339, Ledet. 9. Cranidium and pygidium (lectotype, original of Reed 1906, pl. 5, figs 21&amp;22), GSI 8335, Hweyawt. 10. Cranidium and pygidium (original of Reed 1906, pl. 5, figs 19 and 23), GSI 8334, Hweyawt. Scale bars = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810320" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810320/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">11</figureCitation>
